00364 class SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES
00365 {
00366   public:
00367     friend class SecurityHelper;    
00369     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() 
00370     {
00371         nSrtpKeyLength = 0 ;
00372         nSmimeKeyLength = 0 ;
00373         nSrtpLevel = SRTP_LEVEL_NONE ;
00374         memset(szSrtpKey, 0, sizeof(szSrtpKey));
00375         memset(szSmimeKeyDer, 0, sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer));
00376         memset(dbLocation, 0, sizeof(dbLocation));
00377         memset(szMyCertNickname, 0, sizeof(szMyCertNickname));
00378         memset(szCertDbPassword, 0, sizeof(szCertDbPassword));
00379     }    
00381     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00382     {
00383         copyData(ref);
00384     }    
00386     virtual ~SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES() { }    
00388     SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& operator=(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00389     {
00390         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00391         copyData(ref);
00392         return *this;
00393     }    
00398     void setSrtpKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00399     {
00400         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSrtpKey);
00401         memcpy(szSrtpKey, szKey, safeLen);
00402         nSrtpKeyLength = safeLen;
00403     }    
00408     void setSmimeKey(const char* szKey, const int length)
00409     {
00410         int safeLen = (length < (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer)) ? length : (int) sizeof(szSmimeKeyDer);
00411         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, szKey, safeLen);
00412         nSmimeKeyLength = safeLen;
00413     }
00417     void setSecurityLevel(SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL security) { nSrtpLevel = security; }
00421     const char* getSrtpKey() const  { return szSrtpKey; }    
00426     const char* getSmimeKey() const { return szSmimeKeyDer; }
00430     const int getSrtpKeyLength() const  { return nSrtpKeyLength; }
00435     const int getSmimeKeyLength() const { return nSmimeKeyLength; }
00439     const int getSecurityLevel() const {return nSrtpLevel;}
00445     const char* getCertDbLocation() const { return dbLocation; }
00446   private:
00447     SIPX_SRTP_LEVEL nSrtpLevel;
00448     char szSrtpKey[MAX_SRTP_KEY_LENGTH];
00449     int  nSrtpKeyLength;    
00450     char szSmimeKeyDer[MAX_SMIME_KEY_LENGTH];
00451     int  nSmimeKeyLength; 
00452     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00453     char dbLocation[256];                         
00454     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00455     char szMyCertNickname[32];   
00456     // internally set private member, use sipxConfigSetSecurityParameters
00457     char szCertDbPassword[MAX_PASSWORD_LENGTH];   
00458     void copyData(const SIPX_SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES& ref)
00459     {
00460         nSrtpLevel = ref.nSrtpLevel;
00461         nSrtpKeyLength = ref.nSrtpKeyLength;
00462         nSmimeKeyLength = ref.nSmimeKeyLength;
00463         memcpy(szSrtpKey, ref.szSrtpKey, ref.nSrtpKeyLength);
00464         memcpy(szSmimeKeyDer, ref.szSmimeKeyDer, ref.nSmimeKeyLength);
00465         strncpy(dbLocation, ref.dbLocation, sizeof(dbLocation) - 1);
00466         strncpy(szMyCertNickname, ref.szMyCertNickname, sizeof(szMyCertNickname) - 1);
00467         strncpy(szCertDbPassword, ref.szCertDbPassword, sizeof(szCertDbPassword) - 1);
00468     }
00469 };

00520 struct SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY
00521 {
00523     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY()
00524     {
00525         cbSize = sizeof(SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY);
00526         type = SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE_TYPE;
00527         handle = NULL;
00528     }
00530     ~SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY()
00531     {
00532         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00533         {
00534 #ifdef      _WIN32
00535             if (handle) ((IUnknown*)handle)->Release();
00536 #endif              
00537         }
00538     }
00539     
00541     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00542     {
00543         copy(ref);
00544     }
00546     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& operator=(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00547     {
00548         // check for assignment to self
00549         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00550         copy(ref);
00551         return *this;
00552     }    
00553         
00554     int cbSize;                     
00555     SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY_TYPE type;   
00556     union
00557     {
00558         SIPX_WINDOW_HANDLE handle;  
00559         IBaseFilter* filter;        
00560     };
00561 private:
00562     void copy(const SIPX_VIDEO_DISPLAY& ref)
00563     {
00564         cbSize = ref.cbSize;
00565         type = ref.type;
00566         handle = ref.handle;
00567         if (type == DIRECT_SHOW_FILTER)
00568         {
00569 #ifdef      _WIN32
00570             // we should addRef here.
00571             if (handle) ((IBaseFilter*)handle)->AddRef();
00572 #endif            
00573         }
00574     }
00575     
00576 };

00590 struct SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS
00591 {
00593     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS()
00594     {
00595         memset((void*)cInterface, 0, sizeof(cInterface));
00596         memset((void*)cIpAddress, 0, sizeof(cIpAddress));
00597         memset((void*)cCustomTransportName, 0, sizeof(cCustomTransportName));
00598         memset((void*)cCustomRouteID, 0, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00599         eContactType = CONTACT_AUTO;
00600         eTransportType = TRANSPORT_UDP ;
00601         id = 0;
00602         iPort = -1;
00603     }
00605     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00606     {
00607         strcpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface);
00608         strcpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress);
00609         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00610         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00611         id = ref.id;
00612         iPort = ref.iPort;
00613         strncpy(cCustomTransportName, ref.cCustomTransportName, 32);
00614         strncpy(cCustomRouteID, ref.cCustomRouteID, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00615     }
00617     SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& operator=(const SIPX_CONTACT_ADDRESS& ref)
00618     {
00619         // check for assignment to self
00620         if (this == &ref) return *this;
00621         strcpy(cInterface, ref.cInterface);
00622         strcpy(cIpAddress, ref.cIpAddress);
00623         eContactType = ref.eContactType;
00624         eTransportType = ref.eTransportType;
00625         id = ref.id;
00626         iPort = ref.iPort;
00627         strncpy(cCustomTransportName, ref.cCustomTransportName, sizeof(cCustomTransportName));
00628         strncpy(cCustomRouteID, ref.cCustomRouteID, sizeof(cCustomRouteID));
00629         return *this;
00630     }    
00631     
00632     SIPX_CONTACT_ID     id;              
00633     SIPX_CONTACT_TYPE   eContactType ;   
00634     SIPX_TRANSPORT_TYPE eTransportType ; 
00635     char                cInterface[32] ; 
00636     char                cIpAddress[32] ; 
00637     int                 iPort ;          
00638     char                cCustomTransportName[32]; 
00639     char                cCustomRouteID[64] ;
00640 };
